general.description:
Industry consulting specialist in Engineering and Construction.
I find targeted talent that fits skills-needs, strategy and culture of my clients.

I can advise on:
Recruitment methodology;
Executive search;
Industry trends and pipeline;
Business development opportunities (local and abroad); and
Mergers and Acquisitions.

I am a business change management consultant specializing in the holistic analysis, design and improvement of organizations and processes, and the planning and successful management of transformational change.

I have more than 28 years’ experience in management consulting.  My strengths include:

Identifying and analyzing the impacts of disruptive change in markets and technologies on strategic positioning, performance and current operations;

Synthesizing the "big picture" and local consequences to help organizations and people understand the "so what" of change and how they can respond effectively;

Designing and implementing practical change management strategies and improvement action plans;

Communicating with all types of stakeholders, with particular strengths in workshop facilitation and business writing;

Team and individual development, including coaching, mentoring, and the analysis, planning, design, development, delivery and evaluation of training.

I have delivered projects in Australia, Japan, China, Indonesia, Malaysia, Greece, Sweden, New Zealand, Singapore, Hong Kong and the USA in the telecommunications, government, financial services and utilities sectors.  The telecommunications industry has been a particular focus for me, most recently in projects addressing the transformation impacts of IoT, cloud computing, network virtualization and the dawn of 5G networks.

I have spent more than 19 years as a principal business consultant in Ericsson working with mobile and fixed operators and enterprise verticals around the world.  In this role, I have used many industry standards and methods including the eTOM and ITIL process frameworks and Lean Six Sigma.

Before I joined Ericsson, I worked as a team leader in ERP systems implementation in the utilities industry, as a Change Management consultant with Andersen Consulting (Accenture) for more than seven years, and as a journalist on The Age newspaper and in the Federal Parliamentary Press Gallery.

